  "commentary": "With SPX at 6769.36 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6765 (-18.4B) and positive gamma at 6780 (+13.8B), dealers are caught in a critical pivot zone where they're forced to buy any dip toward 6765 but will aggressively sell any push toward 6780. The regime flip into PIN with surging GEX (+114% 1-min) means dealers just flipped to long gamma, creating a powerful mean-reversion setup that should contain moves within this tight 6765-6780 range. Watch 6765 as the key defense level - any break below triggers amplified selling as dealers dump hedges, while 6780 becomes the ceiling where dealer selling intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect tight, choppy trading between 6765-6780 with strong rejection at both levels.",
